While the fluorescent particles effectively down-convert the blue light into longer wavelengths, they will also scatter the light in all directions. In our simulations, 48% of the down-converted light will be backscattered and this is a significant portion that reduces the efficiency of our desired application. To recover this backscattered light, we incorporate a Bragg reflector layer on the surface of the colour converter that is facing the LED. The Bragg reflector layer acts as a bandpass filter that transmits blue light but reflects green and red lights (Fig. S3). While the Bragg reflector performance is angle-dependent, we expect it to improve the conversion efficiency by up to two times. Here, conversion efficiency (ηConversion\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
