By fabricating cap-like FCC pieces with perylene dye embedded into PMMA, affixing a Bragg reflecting layer on the inner side of the cap (similar to the simulation set-up), and then putting them over an OSRAM GD CS8PM1.14 (blue) LED, we tested the optical as well as the electrical response of F-LED. Figure 4a shows the solid-state blue LED, which changes in colour when fitted with green or red FCCs, to become an F-LED (Fig. 4b,c). The F-LEDs and solid-state LEDs are tested by collecting all emissions via an integrating sphere and measuring them with a calibrated spectrometer. From this, we can figure out the radiant energy emitted from the device. With a sourcemeter to supply electrical power to the devices, we can track the electrical power consumption. Ultimately, we can calculate the wall-plug efficiency based on Eq. (2):Figure 4
